# NOTE: GitHub Pages does not support custom headers via _headers file.
# This file is configured for Netlify-style hosting or CDN configurations.
# GitHub Pages uses its own caching policy (typically 10 minutes for assets).
# However, Hugo asset fingerprinting is enabled, which allows safe long-term caching
# when used with a CDN like Cloudflare that respects custom headers.

